<text top="358" left="83" width="206" height="9" font="2">which were still substantially larger than its phys-</text>
<text top="370" left="51" width="238" height="9" font="2">ical value imposing a significant extrapolation to reach the</text>
<text top="383" left="51" width="238" height="9" font="2">physical up- and down-quark mass point. Among the cal-</text>
<text top="395" left="51" width="139" height="9" font="2">culations performed near physical</text>
<text top="395" left="194" width="7" height="9" font="4"><i>m</i></text>
