<text top="507" left="54" width="10" height="9" font="3"><a href="">14</a></text>
<text top="507" left="64" width="85" height="9" font="2">] and FNAL/MILC <a href="">[</a></text>
<text top="507" left="149" width="5" height="9" font="3"><a href="">5</a></text>
<text top="507" left="154" width="135" height="9" font="2">] are extending their calculations</text>
<text top="520" left="51" width="238" height="9" font="2">down to up-down-quark masses at or very close to their phys-</text>
<text top="532" left="51" width="238" height="9" font="2">ical values while still controlling other sources of systematic</text>
<text top="545" left="51" width="238" height="9" font="2">error. Another aspect that is being increasingly addressed</text>
<text top="557" left="51" width="94" height="9" font="2">are electromagnetic and</text>
<text top="555" left="148" width="4" height="13" font="7"><i>(</i></text>
<text top="557" left="151" width="7" height="9" font="4"><i>m</i></text>
<text top="560" left="159" width="4" height="7" font="5"><i>d</i></text>
